                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Rumania/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-20T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1925—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your No. 10, February 18, 6 p.m. The Department is fully informed in regard to
                    funding agreements of Rumania with the Governments named in paragraph 1,
                    Department’s No. 6, and does not wish you to seek information nor to make
                    representations in regard to it at this time. … Department would prefer to have
                    Rumanian Government take the initiative in refunding matter; but in the absence
                    of any indication that such step will be taken, the Department would seriously
                    consider taking vigorous action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
